-- Ukraine May Consider Curbing Russian Car Imports, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 2012-04-27T11:39:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/ukraine-may-consider-curbing-russian-car-imports-vedomosti-says.html
Ukraine may introduce protective
measures against car imports, Vedomosti reported.  The Eurasian Economic Commission is concerned about
Ukraine’s plans, Andrei Slepnyov, a former Russian Deputy
Economy Minister and now the commission’s trade chief, said in a
letter to Ukrainian Economy Minister Petro Poroshenko, Vedomosti
 reported , citing a copy of the letter.  Russia , Belarus and
 Kazakhstan  created a common economic space overseen by the
commission.  Ukraine is one of the biggest export markets for OAO
AvtoVAZ, Russia’s biggest carmaker, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
